        {
          "topic": "Internal exception prioritization tracking",
          "promised_by": "marcus.patel@adatum.com",
          "commitment_date": "2024-06-19T12:00:00-04:00",
          "description": "Marcus to update the Adatum project tracker with status of lower-priority backlog exceptions before the next Northwind call. Intended solely for internal alignment and capacity review; not to be distributed beyond project management.",
          "client_visible": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "date": "2024-06-21T15:00:00-04:00",
      "participants": [
        {
          "name": "Violet Martinez",
          "email": "violet.martinez@northwindtraders.com",
          "role": "Lead Contact, Supply Chain Transformation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Mario Rogers",
          "email": "mario.rogers@adatum.com",
          "role": "Product Manager, Adatum Corporation"
        },
        {
          "name": "Casey Morgan",
          "email": "casey.morgan@adatum.com",
          "role": "Client Success Specialist, Adatum Corporation"
        }
      ],
      "summary_md": "**Project status alignment meeting following dashboard candidate release.** Violet Martinez provided initial feedback from Northwind’s pilot users: positive response on data visualization clarity, but residual frustrations with the responsiveness of the custom alert builder feature (not meeting SLAs during peak loads). Mario Rogers and Casey Morgan discussed immediate engineering mitigation steps. An interim update to alert builder logic was deployed in the dev environment and scheduled for production migration after next regression test. All parties confirmed readiness for go-live pending validation of alerting workflows. Timeline to final acceptance was discussed, with Violet highlighting the need for rapid turnaround of outstanding action items before contractual deadlines.",
